node.title: No new local COVID cases in WA following rave party outbreak sparked by infected backpacker
node.alt: Three men, two of them wearing gowns and PPE, stand outside the RPH COVID clinic.
node.description: Western Australia records noÂ new local cases of COVID-19, with the number of positive cases in the latest outbreak linked to a French backpacker remaining at 10.
node.content:
["Western Australia has recorded no\u00a0new local cases of COVID-19, with the number of infections in the latest outbreak sparked by a\u00a0French backpacker remaining at 10.", "There were 4,911 tests conducted at public and private testing clinics yesterday,\u00a0WA Premier Mark McGowan said in a statement.", "He said to date, 655 close contacts of the original carrier \u2014 case 1133 \u2014 had been identified, with 46 yet to be tested.", "Another 1,109 casual contacts had been identified, with 243 yet to be tested.", "WA recorded three new coronavirus cases among returned overseas travellers, with two in hotel quarantine and one in self-quarantine.", "More to come.", "", "
